    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 2, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🛢️ Iran offered Hormuz first, nukes later, and Trump still hated the menu\n\nThe war diplomacy now has a shipping lane, a blockade and a nuclear file stacked in the wrong order. Very tidy.\n\n- **The proposal:** Reuters reported on May 2 that Iran offered to reopen the Strait of Hormuz and end the U.S. blockade while postponing nuclear talks.\n- **The rejection:** Donald Trump said he was not satisfied and that Tehran was asking for things he could not accept.\n- **The pressure point:** the strait closure has choked roughly 20% of global oil and gas supplies, while Washington warned ships against paying Iran to transit.\n\n*Diplomacy has become a queue-management problem for war, oil and enrichment.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via MarketScreener](https://www.marketscreener.com/news/iran-offers-strait-deal-trump-dissatisfied-but-prefers-non-military-path-ce7f58ded88cff27) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/2/iran-war-whats-happening-on-day-64-as-trump-rejects-tehrans-proposal)\n\n---\n\n## 🕊️ China told the UN that Lebanon's peacekeepers should maybe not leave during the shooting\n\nA brave concept: perhaps remove the fire monitor after the fire stops, not while everyone is debating the definition of ceasefire.\n\n- **The intervention:** China's UN ambassador Fu Cong said on May 2 that the Security Council should re-examine the planned termination of UNIFIL's mandate.\n- **The battlefield:** Al Jazeera and Reuters reported that Israel continues air raids despite a ceasefire, while Hezbollah has responded with rockets and drones.\n- **The toll:** Lebanese authorities say Israeli attacks since March 2 have killed 2,618 people and displaced more than one million; UN officials say at least six peacekeepers have been killed.\n\n*The phrase lesser fire is doing a lot of diplomatic laundering.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera and Reuters](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/2/china-urges-reversal-of-unifil-departure-from-lebanon-as-conflict-escalates)\n\n---\n\n## 🪖 Peru found its citizens in Russia's war and called the recruiter what it is\n\nThe global manpower market for Ukraine keeps producing new euphemisms. Lima went with human trafficking.\n\n- **The probe:** Peru's public prosecutor said on May 2 it is investigating an alleged network that lured citizens with job offers in Russia before they ended up fighting in Ukraine.\n- **The numbers:** a lawyer for families told local TV that 13 Peruvians have died and that about 600 may have been lured since last October.\n- **The diplomacy:** Peru's foreign ministry asked Russia's embassy to clarify the location and wellbeing of Peruvians serving in the Russian military.\n\n*Russia's foreign recruitment pipeline is now generating consular paperwork on another continent.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera and AFP](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/2/peru-probes-trafficking-of-citizens-to-fight-for-russia-in-ukraine)\n\n---\n\n## 🇨🇺 Havana called Trump's new sanctions collective punishment, because subtlety left the island\n\nThe U.S.-Cuba file is back to sanctions, threats and everyone pretending this is a fresh strategic idea.\n\n- **The move:** Reuters, via Al Jazeera, reported that Trump issued an executive order on Friday expanding sanctions on Cuba's government.\n- **The response:** Foreign Minister Bruno Rodriguez called the measures extraterritorial, coercive and a violation of the UN Charter.\n- **The squeeze:** the sanctions target people and groups helping Cuban security forces, while Trump's earlier fuel blockade framework has worsened blackouts on the island.\n\n*Washington has rediscovered pressure politics. Havana has rediscovered the same speech folder.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera and Reuters](https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2026/5/2/havana-slams-new-trump-sanctions-as-collective-punishment-of-cuban-people)\n"
  }
]
